    "title": "April 2026 Q&A: What Trump is Really Like, Repeal Citizens United, Declining US Dollar",
    "channel": "Anthony Scaramucci",
    "description": "We are back with another Open Book Q&A — the episode where you ask, I answer, and nobody's feelings are guaranteed to survive intact. From repealing Citizens United to what Trump is really like behind closed doors, we're getting into all of it today, so let's go.\n\n📚Books mentioned in this episode:\nFear and Fury by Heather Ann Thompson https://amzn.to/428zppO\nRunnin' Down a Dream by Bill Gurley https://amzn.to/425AQFy\nNigel Hamilton's FDR trilogy https://amzn.to/4swtV30\nRick Atkinson's WWII trilogy https://amzn.to/47XqcnV\nThe Visionaries by James Holland https://amzn.to/41xNw85\nAll the Wrong Moves by Anthony Scaramucci https://amzn.to/3Q6beFX\n\nAnthony Scaramucci is the founder and managing partner of SkyBridge, a global alternative investment firm, and founder and chairman of SALT, a global thought leadership forum and venture studio.\n\nPre-order my next book, All the Wrong Moves: How Three Catastrophic Decisions Led to the Rise of Trump, out on the 17th of September in the UK and the 22nd of September in the US: ⁠https://amzn.to/3Q6beFX\n\nTimestamps\n0:00 April 2026 Open Book Q&A\n0:45 YouTube @h2hcamey - How do we repeal Citizens United? Why did the Dems let that one slip through?\n1:57 Instagram @alastaircampbell - Were you breastfed as a child?\n2:58 LinkedIn Anthony N. - With everything on your plate, what’s your process for capturing key ideas from books and implementing them without overcomplicating things?\n4:25 X @SaucierTer35212 - What is the likelihood of a third party for the moderates?\n5:17 YouTube @brianpinto785 What are your thoughts on what the younger generation will experience?\n6:37 Instagram @rivershannongirl - What is your all-time favorite nonfiction book about WWII?\n8:09 Instagram @tracey.angels - Do you have a new book in the works?\n9:05 X @SageFutures  - Our political system is broken, and those who could fix it are the ones who benefit most by it being broken. 90 million people felt so disenfranchised that they didn’t vote last time. How do we fix this?\n10:48 LinkedIn John Fairfield - How vulnerable do you think the US dollar is relative to other currencies at the moment, and why does it matter?\n11:58 X @evansorg1 - Give us a little background on your famous uncle's motorcycle shop.\n15:02 YouTube @scottkunda-lh7vw As someone who is very new to bitcoin, how is bitcoin useful now and in the future for a common shlub like me?\n15:58 Instagram @maxxgiuliana - How would you suggest a young person go about finding a job where they can learn and grow?\n16:59 LinkedIn Kate Doak - What was Deidre's response to your April Fools Day prank?\n17:45 Instagram @jenmoress - How do you stay looking so young? I thought you were maybe 50.\n18:54 Instagram @samanthajben - Behind the scenes - is there anything human or normal about Trump?\n20:11 Instagram @wsford - How important are real relationships in business?\n20:57 Instagram @the_sub_2003 - What did you dislike the most about working in the Trump White House? & Instagram @mariecolannino - What do you get more enjoyment from - your day job or podcasting?\n22:03 Instagram @nadiamsgill - Why do you still consider yourself a Republican?\n23:21 Instagram @stan.wall.5 - What is one thing everyone can do to make this world a nicer and better place to live?",
